[5] Cholera, diarrhea - Somalia (Awdal, Hiraan)
Date: Sun 14 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: World Health Organization (WHO) [edited]
<http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/RWB.NSF/db900SID/JBRN-6XGHJ8?OpenDocument>

Beletweyne has an increased number of diarrheal cases reported. WHO is
collecting stool samples from these cases.
Yesterday [13 Jan 2007], there were a total of 23 reported cases of acute
watery diarrhea (AWD) in children in the North Western Zone of Somaliland,
Saylac area, bordering Djibouti, also experiencing an outbreak of suspected
cholera. WHO and UNICEF are jointly providing cholera supplies and sending
a joint investigation and response mission to the Somali area.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Somalia can be found at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/somalia.pdf>. The Saylac
area can be found in Awdal, as stated, quite close to Djibouti. Beletweyne
is in Hiraan, further south and much closer to Mogadishu, the capital. -
Mod.LL]
