[6] Gastroenteritis, gala performers - Philippines (Cebu)
Date: Sun 14 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Bangkok Post [edited]
<http://www.bangkokpost.com/breaking_news/previousdetail.php?id=116027>

Food poisoning struck some 60 people who were supposed to perform on Sun 14
Jan 2007 at a gala dinner for Asian leaders meeting in the central
Philippines, organizers said. The performers were rushed to various
hospitals in Cebu province, 585 km south of Manila, early on Sun 14 Jan
2007, after suffering from severe stomachaches, diarrhea, and vomiting.
Arnel Rivera, a doctor with the Philippine Department of Health, said the
victims began to suffer the symptoms late Sat 13 Jan 2007, after eating
their packed food during rehearsals. He said among those hospitalized were
2 international Filipino beauty queens.
The victims were among the performers at a gala show for leaders of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) and their counterparts from
6 east Asian countries. They were discharged hours before the show,
according to Victoriano Lecaros, spokesman for the ASEAN summit.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The short length of the illness without mention of fever suggests
ingestion of preformed enterotoxin, which can be due to _Staphylococcus
aureus_, _Bacillus cereus_ or _Clostridium perfringens_. A map of the
Philippines showing the location of Cebu can be found at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/somalia.pdf>. - Mod.LL]
