[7] Gastroenteritis - Philippines (Ifugao)
Date: Mon 15 Jan 2007
From: Brent Barrett <salbrent@sbcglobal.net>
Source: Manila Standard [edited]
<http://www.manilastandardtoday.com/?page=regions4_jan15_2007>

At least 170 people were stricken by an outbreak of diarrhea caused by
contaminated water in the town of Aguinaldo in Ifugao province, the
Department of Health regional office reported yesterday, 24 Jan 2006.
The regional office said the victims ranged from 4 months to 70 years old,
and public health officials are urging the government to declare a state of
emergency to enable the authorities to deal with the problem.
Aguinaldo Mayor Federico Juguiad Jr. said that the outbreak started in
November 2006, after typhoons Paeng, Queenie, and Reming, and continued
until December 2006, purportedly because of contaminated water.
"We have already received information of a diarrhea outbreak, so we have to
act quickly to prevent further stress to the communities," the mayor said,
specifying the barangays of Awayan, Butac, Chalalo, Damag, Galonogon,
Monggayang, Pojnaan, and Ubao. Pojnaan has the highest number of cases.
Juguiad confirmed health department reports that water and sanitation in
the municipality is compromised by the lack of water resources.
[byline: Roderick Osis]
--
Brent Barrett
Indianapolis, IN
<salbrent@sbcglobal.net>
[A barangay, also known by its former name, the barrio, is the smallest
local government unit in the Philippines and is the native Filipino term
for a village, district, or ward. Municipalities and cities are composed of
barangays.
Ifugao is a landlocked province of the Philippines in the Cordillera
Administrative Region on Luzon. Its location can be seen at:
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ifugao>. ProMED-mail thanks Brent Barrett for
this posting. - Mod.LL]
******
[8] Diarrhea - Spain (Lleida)
Date: Tue 9 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Siglo XXI [trans. Mod.JG, edited]
<http://diariosigloxxi.comnoticia.php/?ts=20070109131011>

An investigation is ongoing into the gastroenteritis outbreak that affected
more than 100 persons in Valencia d'Aneu between 23 and 24 Dec 2006.
There are indications of a possible spill of wastewater into the Bonaigua
River. Also, there may be deficient chlorination of drinking water in this
Alt Aneu area.
A survey by the Health Advisory Board showed that the gastroenteritis
outbreak affected about 65 per cent of the Valencia d'Aneu population and
might have been caused by the presence of a microorganism called _Shigella_
in the drinking water supply.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A commercial map of Spain showing Valencia d'Aneu in Lleida in the
Pyrenees Mountains in north eastern Spain can be found at:
<http://www.ownersdirect.co.uk/Spain-Pyrenees.htm>. As can be seen, the
village is close to France and Andorra. - Mod.LL]
